                  central banks have set interest rates as low as -0.75\%
                  without any such changes, suggesting that, in practice, money
                  demand remains finite even at negative nominal rates. I study
                  optimal monetary policy in this new environment, exploring the
                  central tradeoff: negative rates help stabilize aggregate
